07/09/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutor-General Boris Velchev confirmed on Friday (September 4th) that a few ministers from the former government will be indicted for corruption and embezzlement of public funds.
Interior Minister Tsvetan Tsvetanov had implied as much last week, in response to a report by the national security agency.
Velchev refused to identify the particular officials in question, but said investigations had reached a phase in which indictments have to be issued.
He added that several senior government officials will be charged, including ministers.
(Standart, bTV, Dnevnik - 04/09/09)
